# Documentation

## Docstrings are mandatory

Every module, class, function, and method has a docstring (Google convention). This is enforced by ruff pydocstyle (`D` rules) — undocumented code fails lint. Do not disable `D` rules to bypass; write the docstring.

```python
def extract_movie_keys(candidates: list[str]) -> list[str]:
    """Collect unique movie:{wikipedia_id} keys from retrieval text.

    Args:
        candidates: Raw retrieval passages from LightRAG.

    Returns:
        De-duplicated movie keys in first-seen order.
    """
```

## LangGraph node contract docstring

Every node additionally documents its state contract:

```python
"""One-line purpose.

Reads from state:  <keys>
Writes to state:   <keys>
Side effects:      <none | external API call | DB read>
Failure mode:      <what is returned on exception>
"""
```

## Field descriptions

Every Pydantic model field and `BaseSettings` field has `Field(description=...)`. This powers OpenAPI, env docs, and LLM tool schemas for free.

## Keep docs in sync

When behavior changes, update the relevant `docs/` (C4) page and any affected `docs/setup/*` guide in the same change. Comments explain WHY, not WHAT.
